text: Thierry Lazaro (left) with Louis Alphonse, Duke of Anjou at the eighth centenary commemoration of the battle of Bouvines. Thierry Lazaro (born September 27, 1960) is a member of the National Assembly of France. He represents the Nord department, and is a member of the Union for a Popular Movement. ==References== Category:1960 births Category:Living people Category:Union for a Popular Movement politicians Category:Deputies of the 12th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 14th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic
